DAY-4

Aaj ka kaam (Field Naming & Entity Cleanup)

1) Entity Field Naming Standardization
- User entity me sab fields ko camelCase me convert kiya:
  - uId → id (with @Column(name = "uId") for DB compatibility)
  - uName → name (with @Column(name = "uName"))
  - uEmail → email (with @Column(name = "uEmail"))
  - uPass → password (with @Column(name = "uPass"))
  - uPreferredLanguage → preferredLanguage
  - uCreateAt → createAt, uUpdateAt → updateAt
- Getters/setters bhi update kiye accordingly.

2) Quiz Entity Field Cleanup
- Quiz entity me bhi same approach:
  - qId → id (with @Column(name = "qId"))
  - qSubTopic → subTopic, qDifficulty → difficulty
  - qLanguage → language, qPurpose → purpose
  - qIsActive → isActive (boolean)
  - qCreateAt → createAt, qUpdateAt → updateAt
  - qQuestionsJson → questionsJson

3) Repository Method Name Fixes
- UserRepo me methods update kiye:
  - findByuEmail() → findByEmail()
  - existsByuEmail() → existsByEmail()
  - existsByuName() → existsByName()
- QuizRepo me bhi similar naming conventions apply kiye.

4) Controller Updates
- AuthController me sab references update kiye new field names ke according.
- UserController me getter/setter calls fix kiye.

5) Database Compatibility
- @Column annotations add kiye to keep database schema unchanged.
- Spring JPA ab properly map karega Java camelCase fields to DB snake_case columns.

Testing Status
- Project compiles successfully with BUILD SUCCESS.
- All previous functionality intact with cleaner code.

Next Steps (DAY-5)
- Video entity aur remaining controllers ko fix karna hai.
- Password hashing properly implement karna hai.
- JWT authentication setup start karenge.

